sunSeaProxyMIB.name: sunSeaProxyMIB
sunSeaProxyMIB.description: The MIB used to manage the snmpdx master agent daemon

sunSeaProxyMIBStatusFile.name: sunSeaProxyMIBStatusFile
sunSeaProxyMIBStatusFile.description: This file stores the process id's of all the sub agents that are invoked by the master agent. The purpose of this file is for Master Agent recovery in case the Master Agent dies or is killed. When the Master Agent restarts, the entries in this file will indicate which subagents are spawned by it previously and what were their port numbers.

sunSeaProxyMIBResourceConfigFile.name: sunSeaProxyMIBResourceConfigFile
sunSeaProxyMIBResourceConfigFile.description: This file is exclusively used by the Master Agent. When the Master Agent comes up, it reads this file. This files stores information for all those agents that can be managed by the Master Agent. Each entry in the configuration file also includes the methods for invoking these subagents. It is also possible for a subagent not to have an entry in this configuration file. Such a subagent can dynamically come up and register with the Master Agent when it comes up.

sunSeaProxyMIBConfigurationDir.name: sunSeaProxyMIBConfigurationDir
sunSeaProxyMIBConfigurationDir.description: This is the directory that contains the configuration files for the Master Agent.

sunSeaProxyMIBTrapPort.name: sunSeaProxyMIBTrapPort
sunSeaProxyMIBTrapPort.description: This is the port that master agent opens to receive SNMP trap notifications from various subagents. The master agent forwards these traps to the managers appropriately.

sunCheckSubAgentName.name: sunCheckSubAgentName
sunCheckSubAgentName.description: This variable is of use to the sub agents only. It is used by the sub agents to check with the master to check for duplicate sub agent names.

sunSeaProxyMIBPollInterval.name: sunSeaProxyMIBPollInterval
sunSeaProxyMIBPollInterval.description: This variable speicifies the time interval after which the Master Agent will perform activities other than receiving/sending of SNMP messages. The other activities include trying to find out if there is a change in the resource file, discover if all the agents are responding, and other such routine house keeping activities. This field contains values in seconds.

sunSeaProxyMIBMaxAgentTimeOut.name: sunSeaProxyMIBMaxAgentTimeOut
sunSeaProxyMIBMaxAgentTimeOut.description: The value of this field can be specified in microseconds. This field signifies the max allowed time-out a subagent can request during registration; e.g., when the Master Agent sends a request to a subagent. It waits for some time-out to receive the response. This time-out can be specified in the registration file or can also be set using dynamic registration. If an agent sets this time-out outrageously high, it can create problems for the Master Agent and other agents. To avoid such a problem, the Master Agent can have a policy of specifying a maximum value for which the Master Agent will wait for a response from the subagent. This maximum value of time-out is specified with this variable.

sunSubAgentTable.name: sunSubAgentTable
sunSubAgentTable.description: This table lists all the sub-agents that are registered with the master agent. The list contains the names of all the sub agents that are currently running on the system. Some of these sub agents could be invoked by the master agent and other's could have benn invoked by other means.

sunSubAgentTableIndex.name: sunSubAgentTableIndex
sunSubAgentTableIndex.description: The next available index in sunSubAgentTable.

sunSubAgentEntry.name: sunSubAgentEntry
sunSubAgentEntry.description: An entry in the sub-agent table.

sunSubAgentID.name: sunSubAgentID
sunSubAgentID.description: This is the id for each sub agent that is running and registered with the master agent.

sunSubAgentStatus.name: sunSubAgentStatus
sunSubAgentStatus.description: This variable provides the state of the sub-agent. When the sub-agent is started the state is 'init'. Once the sub-agent has read it's configuration files, but has not registered with the master , the state is 'load'. After the 'load' state the sub-agent goes into 'active' state. In this state the sub-agent has registered with the master agent and would respond to any requests from the master agent and can also generate traps.

sunSubAgentTimeout.name: sunSubAgentTimeout
sunSubAgentTimeout.description: The max. time for which the master agent would wait for a sub-agent to complete the request. The value is specified in usec.

sunSubAgentPortNumber.name: sunSubAgentPortNumber
sunSubAgentPortNumber.description: The port number of the sub-agent on which it listens for requests from the master agent.

sunSubAgentRegistrationFile.name: sunSubAgentRegistrationFile
sunSubAgentRegistrationFile.description: This is the registration file of a sub-agent. Each sub-agent has its own registration file. This file contains information pertinent to each agent. The information includes the name of the agent, the subtree OIDs managed by the respective agent, request time out, the preferred port number, etc.

sunSubAgentAccessControlFile.name: sunSubAgentAccessControlFile
sunSubAgentAccessControlFile.description: This is a file that has the access control information for each sub agent. It stores SNMP-related community information. Every subagent and a Master Agent can have its own access control file.

sunSubAgentExecutable.name: sunSubAgentExecutable
sunSubAgentExecutable.description: The executable file of the sub-agent.

sunSubAgentVersionNum.name: sunSubAgentVersionNum
sunSubAgentVersionNum.description: The version number of the sub-agent.

sunSubAgentProcessID.name: sunSubAgentProcessID
sunSubAgentProcessID.description: The process id of the sub-agent.

sunSubAgentName.name: sunSubAgentName
sunSubAgentName.description: The name of the sub-agent. This is assigned by the user.

sunSubAgentSystemUpTime.name: sunSubAgentSystemUpTime
sunSubAgentSystemUpTime.description: The system up time of the sub-agent.

sunSubAgentWatchDogTime.name: sunSubAgentWatchDogTime
sunSubAgentWatchDogTime.description: This timeout is used by the Master Agent to determine if the subagent is up or not. The Master Agent will poll the subagent only if there has been no activity between the Master Agent and the subagent for this specified interval. This interval is specified in seconds.

sunSubTreeConfigurationTable.name: sunSubTreeConfigurationTable
sunSubTreeConfigurationTable.description: This is the table of subtree registration requests made by the sub agents. The enteries in this table also include the sub tree OID's of those agents that are invkoed by the master agent. This table thus consists of enteries as configured in the sub agent registration files. These sub tree OID's are flattened into a OID sub tree dispatch table in the master agent which is also defined in this MIB.

sunSubTreeConfigurationTableIndex.name: sunSubTreeConfigurationTableIndex
sunSubTreeConfigurationTableIndex.description: The next available index in sunSubTreeConfigurationTable.

sunSubTreeIndex.name: sunSubTreeIndex
sunSubTreeIndex.description: The index of the table registration.

sunSubTreeOID.name: sunSubTreeOID
sunSubTreeOID.description: The oid of the subtree table that is being registered. A sub agent can have multiple sub tree oid's registered as seperate enteries.

sunSubTreeStartColumn.name: sunSubTreeStartColumn
sunSubTreeStartColumn.description: Starting column of the sub table.

sunSubTreeEndColumn.name: sunSubTreeEndColumn
sunSubTreeEndColumn.description: Ending column of the sub table.

sunSubTreeStartRow.name: sunSubTreeStartRow
sunSubTreeStartRow.description: Starting row of the sub table.

sunSubTreeEndRow.name: sunSubTreeEndRow
sunSubTreeEndRow.description: Ending row of the sub table.

sunSubTreeStatus.name: sunSubTreeStatus
sunSubTreeStatus.description: The variable allows to activate or delete the enteries in this table.

sunSubTreeDispatchTable.name: sunSubTreeDispatchTable
sunSubTreeDispatchTable.description: This table lists all the OID enteries that are used by the master agent to dispatch the requests to the sub agents. This table is based on the sub-tree registration configured in the sub agents registration files.

sunSubTreeDispatchTableIndex.name: sunSubTreeDispatchTableIndex
sunSubTreeDispatchTableIndex.description: The next available index in sunSubTreeDispatchTable.

sunSubTreeDispatchIndex.name: sunSubTreeDispatchIndex
sunSubTreeDispatchIndex.description: The index of the dispatch table entry.

sunSubTreeDispatchStatus.name: sunSubTreeDispatchStatus
sunSubTreeDispatchStatus.description: The variable allows to activate or delete the enteries in this table.
